website_summaries.verdict: If you're taller than average, this jump rope is sure to fit the bill with its lengthy cable and generous handles.
pros: Features foam grips for secure hold
Perfect for speed jumping and double unders
cons: Longer handles can feel awkward for some

customer_reviews.title: the company is super friendly and helpful (a rare experience these days)
customer_reviews.text: Remember when you were little, and you were learning how to jump rope, and you sometimes caught the rope on your toes or feet? Well, my only complaint about this is that it hurts REALLY badly when you hit yourself. That being said, the ball bearings make this jump rope the smoothest one my husband and I have ever had, AND the length is adjustable, so we can both use it without me having to wrap one end around my wrist to compensate for the height difference. On top of that, the company is super friendly and helpful (a rare experience these days). I guess the foot-whippings just give us incentive to get better, right?
customer_reviews.author: ElleArby

customer_reviews.title: Not designed for heavy use.
customer_reviews.text: I liked using the rope when it worked, but unfortunately, I ran into several problems early on that have forced me to buy a different one. First, the rope cable cracked within 1 week (likely in the area where the cable makes contact with the floor, although I only used it on rubber mats and smooth hardwood floors). Subsequently, the swivel handles repeatedly jammed. I was able to pry them free with a pair of pliers, but after the third time, I concluded that this rope is just not built for heavy use. I have owned it for only about 1 month. ----
customer_reviews.author: Anon

customer_reviews.title: I like it quite a bit.
customer_reviews.text: I really like how it comes with an adjustable cable. I think it was 10 or 11 feet and you can cut the cable and adjust it to your preference. It also comes with a second cable for incase you cut it too short or if you just want to have two different lengths. I am quite happy with this product so far... now if only I can get my fat butt to jump without tripping my self up.... time for some more practice.... *sigh*...
customer_reviews.author: K.M.

customer_reviews.title: Great rope and great price
customer_reviews.text: Finally a good rope for dubs! I’ve been struggling with them for a while, and would always whip myself pretty hard with other ropes. This one is coated so it doesn’t hurt so much, plus the rope turns smoothly and doesn’t get deformed. The price would already be unbelievable for the rope alone, but it also includes a set of extras. Such a great deal. After I bought it, my gym buddies have tried it out and 4 of them have gotten them already. Great product.
customer_reviews.author: Julie Valbuena

customer_reviews.title: Just what I was Looking For
customer_reviews.text: I was looking for a beginner rope to begin warming up with and using between sets during my workout, and this one couldn't be more perfect. For starters, it's super light and comes in a carry case that fits easily in my gym bag with the rest of my gear. The rope itself is thin steel cable and coated which is great for speed rope. The cable is simple to size, and you'll get emailed instructions on proper sizing. The handles are durable and will last forever. The best part is that you get 2 ropes, in the even that the first gets worn out. Definitely worth the purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Jeremy S.

customer_reviews.title: Great product, great value, excellent service
customer_reviews.text: This rope is excellent. For the cost it's the best rope I've found. Handles have a nice weight to them. The cable is coated which keeps it from fraying or unraveling as well as helps the tiger stripes not be so bad. The extra cable and rubber ends were a great detail. Doubled unders went from 5 unbroken to being more fun, smoother, and I'm up to 15+ The rope just makes it more fun to practice and consistency has done wonders.
customer_reviews.author: Rollie2

customer_reviews.title: Top Notch Jump Rope
customer_reviews.text: This is a top notch peice of gear. It comes with an extra cable and securing hardware. The hardware is excellent quality. I especially like the handles. The bearings make using it very easy. It has a very smooth feel as the cable rotates. Jeff, the founder of 321 STRONG, followed up with me right after delivery to make sure I was happy. You don't see customer service like that every day. If you are looking for a top of the line cable jump rope, then you should look no further. To make things even better, you won't beat the price
customer_reviews.author: Dave

customer_reviews.title: Not Recommended: 90 Handle keeps locking up
customer_reviews.text: Overall the quality of construction appears good but I would not recommend this rope. The first time I used it one of the degree handles locked up and the cord kept twisting around the handle based on the top not free spinning. I tried adjust the screw and loosening the swivel head yet it keeps locking up. I am now shopping for a replacement rope from somewhere else. Also as a minor issue, I never got the promised e-book. However I was able to easily find it by going to 321 Strong’s website. I would say buy a different rope.
customer_reviews.author: Molly S Nestor

customer_reviews.title: Made a huge difference
customer_reviews.text: I was struggling to keep the exercise going with my old rope. This rope made a huge difference. It is of high quality. It is easily adjustable. The videos that they provide help you to adjust it correctly and to get going with this rope. Very glad that I purchased this jumprope.
customer_reviews.author: Timothy Sorber

customer_reviews.title: Garbage. Don't buy.
customer_reviews.text: Two of these have broken after less than 2 months of use. The latest one broke after less than 2 weeks. Guarbage product, garbage quality. DONT BUY. Just ponied up the $ for a rogue speed rope. I can't risk having these things break in the middle of a workout so easily.
customer_reviews.author: Michael Cosmi

customer_reviews.title: Great customer service
customer_reviews.text: Product is good but the customer service is excellent. I initially had an issue with my first order for some reason the handles came apart in the middle of my work out so I reached out to Jeff and told him about my disappointing experience. He immediately got back to me and already refunded the charge to my account. He offered to send replacement parts but I just decided to reorder them as I was happy with the product before things started coming apart. My jump rope is good now and I am super happy.
customer_reviews.author: easymac

customer_reviews.title: this is a great product especially for the price
customer_reviews.text: I don't really write reviews, this is a great product especially for the price. I also have an RPM rope and I got this after my cables frayed out and a bearing flew off the end, I borrowed one from somebody at the gym. Even with a coated cable it is easily as fast. I was impressed when it showed up with a storage bag, extra cable and a hardware kit - I'm sure that's all in the product description but I didn't read it, I just ordered the rope because I knew it was the one I was looking for. If you are working on double unders I highly recommend getting one of these.

customer_reviews.title: Did Not Last
customer_reviews.text: I was excited to receive this jump rope - upon first glance, it looked well built and like it would be a smooth rope. Upon my first use of it, however, one of the handles started to fall apart. I had to use gorilla glue as a workaround. This worked well enough until the other handle would not rotate smoothly (not the glued handle) which caused the rope to wrap around the handle upon use. I wanted to enjoy this product but the quality wasn’t there.
customer_reviews.author: Nicolle Franco

customer_reviews.title: I really like using this rope
customer_reviews.text: I really like using this rope. Helped me get my double unders more consistent. The long rope and easy adjustable length is a high point for sure. One of my handles seized up on the second workout while I was using it. I contacted the seller and asked if I could fix it or return the rope. Within a day, Jeff responded and said he would send me a replacement. I am very pleased with all aspects of this purchase, even with the small malfunction. Thanks!

I would not recommend this product.
